member.name: T:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgE441x_A_09_01.AgE441x
member.summary: E441x EPM Series Power Meters

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgE441x_A_09_01.SCPI.SCPIClass.ABORt
member.summary: The ABORt command removes the specified channel from the "wait-for-trigger" state and places it in the "idle" state.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgE441x_A_09_01.SCPI.SCPIClass.CONFigure
member.summary: This query returns the present configuration of the specified window.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgE441x_A_09_01.SCPI.SCPIClass.CLS
member.summary: The *CLS (CLear Status) command clears the status data structures.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgE441x_A_09_01.SCPI.SCPIClass.DDT
member.summary: The *DDT (Define Device Trigger) command determines the power meter's response to a GET (Group Execute Trigger) message or *TRG common command.The query returns the action which is performed on receipt of a GET or *TRG.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgE441x_A_09_01.SCPI.SCPIClass.ESE
member.summary: The *ESE (Event Status Enable) <NRf> command sets the Standard Event Status Enable Register.The query returns the current contents of the Standard Event Status Enable Register.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgE441x_A_09_01.SCPI.SCPIClass.ESR
member.summary: The *ESR? query returns the contents of the Standard Event Status Register then clears it.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgE441x_A_09_01.SCPI.SCPIClass.IDN
member.summary: The *IDN? query allows the power meter to identify itself.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgE441x_A_09_01.SCPI.SCPIClass.OPC
member.summary: The *OPC (OPeration Complete) command causes the power meter to set the operation complete bit in the Standard Event Status Register when all pending device operations have completed. The query places an ASCII 1 in the output queue when all pending device operations have completed.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgE441x_A_09_01.SCPI.SCPIClass.OPT
member.summary: The *OPT? query reports the options installed in the power meter

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgE441x_A_09_01.SCPI.SCPIClass.RCL
member.summary: The *RCL <NRf> (ReCaLl) command restores the state of the power meter from the specified save/recall register.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgE441x_A_09_01.SCPI.SCPIClass.RST
member.summary: The *RST (ReSeT) command places the power meter in a known state.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgE441x_A_09_01.SCPI.SCPIClass.SAV
member.summary: The *SAV <NRf> (SAVe) command stores the current state of the power meter in the specified register.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgE441x_A_09_01.SCPI.SCPIClass.SRE
member.summary: The *SRE <NRf> command sets the Service Request Enable register bits. The query returns the contents of bits 0 to 5 and bit 7 of the Service Request Enable Register.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgE441x_A_09_01.SCPI.SCPIClass.STB
member.summary: The *STB? (STatus Byte) query returns bit 0 to 5 and bit 7 of the power meter's status byte and returns the Master Summary Status (MSS) as bit 6.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgE441x_A_09_01.SCPI.SCPIClass.TRG
member.summary: The *TRG (TRiGger) command triggers all channels that are in the "wait-for-trigger" state. It has the same effect as Group Execute Trigger (GET).

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgE441x_A_09_01.SCPI.SCPIClass.TST
member.summary: The *TST? (TeST) query causes the power meter to perform the GP-IB self test which takes approximately 30 seconds.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgE441x_A_09_01.SCPI.SCPIClass.WAI
member.summary: The *WAI (WAIt) command causes the power meter to wait

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgE441x_A_09_01.Transport.TransportClass.DefaultTimeout
member.summary:
DefaultTimeout specifies the timeout, in milliseconds, for queries issued to this instrument.
A timeout will occur if there is no response from the instrument within the specified duration.
A value of -1 is used to specify no timeout.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgE441x_A_09_01.Transport.TransportClass.ErrorQueryBehavior
member.summary:
ErrorQueryBehavior specifies whether Command Expert automatically retrieves errors from the instrument's SCPI error queue by sending SYST:ERR? queries. Command Expert displays errors retrieved from the SCPI error queue in the Results column of the Sequence pane.
The supported values for ErrorQueryBehavior are:
None - SYST:ERR? queries will not be automatically sent.
ErrorQueryPerCommand - a :SYST:ERR? query will be sent after each command, and after each query that times out.
ErrorQueryPerCommandAndQuery - a :SYST:ERR? query will be sent after each command and after each query.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgE441x_A_09_01.Transport.TransportClass.OpcBehavior
member.summary:
OpcBehavior specifies whether Command Expert automatically sends a *OPC? query after each command.
The supported values for OpcBehavior are:
None - *OPC? queries will not be automatically sent to the instrument.
OpcPerCommand - an *OPC? query will be sent after every command, and no further commands or queries will be sent until the *OPC? returns.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgE441x_A_09_01.Transport.TransportClass.OmitDefaultKeywords
member.summary: OmitDefaultKeywords specifies whether to omit default keywords when sending SCPI commands.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgE441x_A_09_01.Transport.TransportClass.UseShortFormKeywords
member.summary: UseShortFormKeywords specifies whether to use the short form of SPCI keywords when sending SCPI commands.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgE441x_A_09_01.Transport.TransportClass.IgnoredErrors
member.summary:
IgnoredErrors is a string that specifies the list of SCPI error codes that will be ignored during execution.
For example, setting IgnoredErrors to the string "1:100,301:400" specifies that error codes from 1 to 100 inclusive and 301 to 400 inclusive will be ignored.
When setting IgnoredErrors, the input string should contain a list of zero or more items, separated by commas. Each item is either an integer, or a range of the form X:Y where X and Y are integers. The integers can be positive, 0, or negative.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgE441x_A_09_01.Transport.TransportClass.AddToIgnoredErrors
member.summary:
AddToIgnoredErrors adds the specified error codes to IgnoredErrors (the list of SCPI error codes ignored during execution).
For example, invoking AddToIgnoredErrors with the string "1:100,301:400" will add the error codes from 1 to 100 inclusive and 301 to 400 inclusive.
When invoking AddToIgnoredErrors, the input string should contain a list of zero or more items, separated by commas. Each item is either an integer, or a range of the form X:Y where X and Y are integers. The integers can be positive, 0, or negative.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgE441x_A_09_01.Transport.TransportClass.RemoveFromIgnoredErrors
member.summary:
RemoveFromIgnoredErrors removes the specified error codes from IgnoredErrors (the list of SCPI error codes ignored during execution).
For example, invoking RemoveFromIgnoredErrors with the string "1:100,301:400" will remove the error codes from 1 to 100 inclusive and 301 to 400 inclusive.
When invoking RemoveFromIgnoredErrors, the input string should contain a list of zero or more items, separated by commas. Each item is either an integer, or a range of the form X:Y where X and Y are integers. The integers can be positive, 0, or negative.
